<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  entitlements.plist — hardened-runtime entitlements for the Centinelo Phone
  macOS .app. Applied by build-macos's MANUAL codesign step (the one that
  runs AFTER package-official.sh injects core-engine into the .app, which is
  why Tauri's own signing is disabled and we sign by hand - see
  .github/workflows/release.yml's "Codesign the .app in depth" step and
  shell/README.md "Apple code signing & notarization").

  Minimal set for a SIP softphone under hardened runtime:
    - device.audio-input : the mic (coreaudio captures audio for calls).
    - network.client     : outbound SIP/RTP/WS to the PBX.
    - network.server     : SIP listens on a local port (the baresip sidecar
                           binds a UDP/TCP SIP socket).

  NOTE on com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation: deliberately
  ABSENT. Hardened runtime's Library Validation requires every loaded dylib
  be signed by Apple or the SAME Team ID as the main executable. The
  core-engine/baresip modules AND any premium dylib are all codesigned in
  the same step with the SAME Developer ID Application certificate (same Team
  ID), so library validation passes WITHOUT weakening it. If a future build
  ever loaded a dylib signed by a DIFFERENT team, that entitlement would
  become necessary - do not add it preemptively; it weakens the runtime.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>com.apple.security.device.audio-input</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.network.server</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
